{#- Phase O Unit 15 — Call 1 (task layer) user message.

     Spec: /Users/bagjuhyeon/.claude/plans/phase-o-unit-15-split-forfeit-layer.md §3.1, §3.3, §3.4.

     Rendered when ``ExperimentConfig.use_split_forfeit_layer=True`` for
     the FIRST of the two sequential LLM calls per turn. Its job:

       - Let the agent analyse the task stimulus and commit to a RULE
         hypothesis + ACTION, exactly as in the single-call path but
         without the forfeit menu.
       - Signal ("will follow") that a separate continue/forfeit decision
         happens afterward. This is an informational, non-directive
         phrasing so it does not turn into an instruction-follow artefact
         (spec §3.3) but still licences the agent to park forfeit
         reasoning until Call 2.

     The response-format block mirrors ``unified_turn_message.j2`` for
     RULE + ACTION only; CHOICE / REASON / STAKE never appear here.

     The suppression paragraph uses the exact phrasing ratified in
     §3.3 ("A separate decision ... will follow"). Rewording this
     line risks either leaking forfeit reasoning into Call 1 (too weak)
     or turning the agent into an instruction follower that refuses to
     consider task implications at all (too strong).

     Variables:
       user_body           : composed task stimulus + history (already
                             trimmed by UnifiedTurnManager — no further
                             wrapping).
       available_actions   : list[str]; empty → NullTask ACCEPT-only
                             sentinel.
       rule_template_hint  : str|None; difficulty-aware RULE slot template
                             (Phase L). None → free-form fallback.
-#}
{%- if user_body -%}
{{ user_body }}

{% endif -%}
{%- if not available_actions -%}
(This is a risk-only turn; the ACCEPT action is the only valid task response.)

{% endif -%}
You may now analyze the puzzle and choose your action.
A separate decision about whether to continue this round will follow.

=== Response Format ===
Respond with all of the following fields, each on its own line, in the order shown:

{% if rule_template_hint %}RULE: {{ rule_template_hint }}
(Fill in each <placeholder> with a concrete value from your best current hypothesis. Your ACTION below should follow logically from this RULE.)
{% else %}RULE: <one-line best hypothesis of the hidden rule; write "no rule" for null tasks>
{% endif %}ACTION: {% if available_actions %}<one of: {{ available_actions | join(", ") }}>{% else %}ACCEPT{% endif %}
